# Repo conventions

Living document for cross-cutting conventions that aren't worth a full ADR. When a decision is big or
hard to reverse, write an ADR in `docs/decisions/` instead and link it here.

## Commit messages — Conventional Commits

Format: `<type>(<optional scope>): <imperative summary>` with an optional body and footer.

| Type | When |
|---|---|
| `feat` | New user- or developer-facing capability. |
| `fix` | Bug fix. |
| `refactor` | Restructuring with no behavior change. |
| `perf` | Performance improvement. |
| `test` | Tests only. |
| `docs` | Documentation only (README, ADRs, comments). |
| `build` | Build system, dependencies, Docker, package manifests. |
| `ci` | CI/CD configuration. |
| `chore` | Housekeeping that fits nowhere else. |
| `revert` | Reverting a previous commit. |

**Scopes** (suggested): {{SCOPES}}. Use when a commit clearly belongs to one component; omit when
cross-cutting.

**Breaking changes:** append `!` after the type/scope and add a `BREAKING CHANGE:` footer.

Why this style: machine-parseable (enables changelogs/semver later), forces a deliberate type up front,
and is industry-standard so onboarding cost is near zero.

